What happened on the 30th of November?

1280
01:45:16,250 --> 01:45:21,875
Sir, on that day, Rishu's parents
left for Bareilly, to attend a wedding.

1281
01:45:22,833 --> 01:45:27,083
Remember to turn off the gas valve,
or you'll end up blowing up the house.

1282
01:45:27,167 --> 01:45:28,375
-Bye.
-Take care.

1283
01:45:28,458 --> 01:45:29,417
Bye. You also take care.

1284
01:45:29,500 --> 01:45:32,833
We had invited Rishu's friends
over that day.

1285
01:45:32,917 --> 01:45:34,792
Aren't your friends coming over today?

1286
01:45:34,875 --> 01:45:39,542
I had asked Rishu to get a few things,
on his way back from work.

1287
01:45:39,625 --> 01:45:41,917
I've already bought mutton.
Don't forget the spices.

1288
01:45:42,000 --> 01:45:43,833
Send me a list of what you need.

1289
01:45:47,417 --> 01:45:50,125
<i>-But Rishu returned early.</i>
-I've got everything.

1290
01:45:50,208 --> 01:45:53,792
<i>And he saw me talking to Neel.</i>

1291
01:45:53,875 --> 01:45:56,250
Rishu, he…

1292
01:45:57,667 --> 01:45:59,667
Welcome home, Rishu.

1293
01:45:59,750 --> 01:46:03,083
Why haven't you told him
that you're leaving with me?

1294
01:46:03,167 --> 01:46:04,042
Stop lying.

1295
01:46:04,125 --> 01:46:05,792
He's here to talk about something, Rishu.

1296
01:46:05,875 --> 01:46:07,583
Rani, go outside and let us sort this out.

1297
01:46:07,667 --> 01:46:11,042
<i>I tried to explain everything to Rishu.</i>

1298
01:46:11,125 --> 01:46:12,750
Go, Rani.
We are just talking, don't worry.

1299
01:46:13,458 --> 01:46:14,542
<i>But he wouldn't listen.</i>

1300
01:46:15,292 --> 01:46:16,542
<i>He insisted.</i>

1301
01:46:19,000 --> 01:46:24,667
<i>And I left to go to the market.</i>

1302
01:46:25,917 --> 01:46:27,042
Rickshaw!

1303
01:46:27,125 --> 01:46:29,875
<i>As I left the house,the door was left open…</i>

1304
01:46:29,958 --> 01:46:31,958
Tell Rishu to lock the door.

1305
01:46:32,042 --> 01:46:33,708
Rishu! Lock the door.

1306
01:46:33,792 --> 01:46:34,875
<i>I saw Ruhina.</i>

1307
01:46:34,958 --> 01:46:36,708
I am making <i>kheer</i> today.
I'll send some over.

1308
01:46:36,792 --> 01:46:40,667
-That's great.
-<i>And I got into the rickshaw.</i>

1309
01:46:40,750 --> 01:46:44,500
<i>I had a tiff with the butcher.</i>

1310
01:46:44,583 --> 01:46:45,625
Your knife looks rusted.

1311
01:46:45,708 --> 01:46:47,958
There's no way our knives are rusted.

1312
01:46:48,042 --> 01:46:50,125
Give it to me,
I'll get it cut from somewhere else.

1313
01:46:51,042 --> 01:46:53,375
<i>So I went to another butcher,</i>

1314
01:46:53,958 --> 01:46:57,208
<i>got him to cut the mutton,and was on my way back home.</i>

1315
01:46:57,792 --> 01:47:00,167
<i>I gave a few pieces of muttonto the stray dogs.</i>

1316
01:47:14,708 --> 01:47:15,583
Rishu!

1317
01:47:16,417 --> 01:47:17,333
Rishu!

1318
01:47:19,625 --> 01:47:20,458
Rishu!

1319
01:47:30,042 --> 01:47:34,333
Her heartbeat is fast even
when answering general questions.

1320
01:47:34,875 --> 01:47:36,000
Which is normal.

1321
01:47:36,708 --> 01:47:38,708
But there's no change
when I ask the other questions.

1322
01:47:39,292 --> 01:47:41,083
It's difficult to come to a conclusion.

1323
01:47:42,333 --> 01:47:43,542
Now what?

1324
01:47:45,000 --> 01:47:46,333
We can do one thing.

1325
01:47:47,167 --> 01:47:50,667
I'll ask her questions
she can reply, with a yes or a no.

1326
01:47:51,500 --> 01:47:52,375
Okay.

1327
01:48:03,542 --> 01:48:06,583
Does she always wear these shoes?

1328
01:48:08,417 --> 01:48:09,250
Why?

1329
01:48:10,208 --> 01:48:11,208
Got it. Let's go.

1330
01:48:11,833 --> 01:48:13,917
Remove your shoes, madam.

1331
01:48:23,625 --> 01:48:24,958
Look at this, sir.

1332
01:48:25,042 --> 01:48:26,833
She has put a nail inside the shoe.

1333
01:48:27,917 --> 01:48:29,583
This would have caused her pain.

1334
01:48:30,167 --> 01:48:32,458
And pain quickens the heartbeat.

1335
01:48:33,417 --> 01:48:37,042
Now she'll claim
that she was unaware of this.

1336
01:48:37,875 --> 01:48:41,000
Get her to talk, Mishra.

1337
01:48:44,583 --> 01:48:46,417
Is your name Rani Kashyap?

1338
01:48:49,417 --> 01:48:50,250
Yes.

1339
01:48:50,333 --> 01:48:51,958
Are you 28 years old?

1340
01:48:52,458 --> 01:48:53,625
Yes.

1341
01:48:53,708 --> 01:48:55,750
Did you kill your husband?

1342
01:49:00,417 --> 01:49:01,625
No.

1343
01:49:07,917 --> 01:49:10,750
Were you having an affair
with Neel Tripathi?

1344
01:49:11,833 --> 01:49:12,667
Yes.

1345
01:49:12,750 --> 01:49:15,125
Did your lover kill your husband?

1346
01:49:17,833 --> 01:49:18,667
I don't know.

1347
01:49:22,917 --> 01:49:25,583
Did you murder your husband?

1348
01:49:27,125 --> 01:49:28,458
No, I didn't.

1349
01:49:40,625 --> 01:49:42,458
<i>Sir, I am convincedthat she has committed the murder.</i>

1350
01:49:42,542 --> 01:49:44,625
She knows where her lover is.
The machine hasn't…

1351
01:49:44,708 --> 01:49:45,875
Enough of this nonsense.

1352
01:49:46,708 --> 01:49:50,083
Close Rani's case and start investigating
the honor killing case.

1353
01:51:12,458 --> 01:51:15,917
<i>Madam left and the case file was closed.</i>

1354
01:51:17,250 --> 01:51:19,875
<i>But this case will alwaysremain open for me.</i>

1355
01:51:20,625 --> 01:51:24,583
<i>Everyone said that I'd takenthis case very personally…</i>

1356
01:51:25,583 --> 01:51:29,333
<i>Five years went by and I got transferred.</i>

1357
01:51:33,000 --> 01:51:34,667
-Have you taken everything?
-Yes, I have.

1358
01:51:36,583 --> 01:51:38,250
I've kept your luggage inside, sir.

1359
01:51:38,833 --> 01:51:40,750
Best wishes for your new posting.

1360
01:51:40,833 --> 01:51:42,167
We'll miss you, sir.

1361
01:51:43,083 --> 01:51:44,625
-Good to know!
-Thank you, sir.

1362
01:51:44,708 --> 01:51:46,667
-How much is it?
-Won't you share some?

1363
01:51:46,750 --> 01:51:48,042
Give some to Uncle.

1364
01:51:48,125 --> 01:51:49,667
It's okay…

1365
01:51:50,375 --> 01:51:51,583
What about me?

1366
01:51:51,667 --> 01:51:54,708
Sir, have you read Dinesh Pandit's novels?

1367
01:51:54,792 --> 01:51:57,958
DINESH PANDIT
<i>WRATH OF KASAULI</i>

1368
01:51:58,542 --> 01:52:00,333
<i>Dinesh Pandit writes,</i>

1369
01:52:01,125 --> 01:52:05,833
"Eternal love will always be
stained with a few drops of blood!"

1370
01:52:08,333 --> 01:52:11,542
<i>Savitri had won overBhairav's heart once again.</i>

1371
01:52:12,125 --> 01:52:15,958
<i>But Bhairav didn't knowthat he had one last hurdle to cross,</i>

1372
01:52:16,542 --> 01:52:18,917
<i>before he could get her.</i>

1373
01:52:22,625 --> 01:52:28,667
<i>Cardamom, cloves, raisins,almonds, and… Rishu.</i>

1374
01:52:29,833 --> 01:52:32,708
<i>From a different perspective,Rani can be an endless debate.</i>

1375
01:52:33,417 --> 01:52:36,583
<i>One with accusations and insults for me…</i>

1376
01:52:37,333 --> 01:52:39,833
<i>But I want to have this debate…all my life.</i>

1377
01:52:40,875 --> 01:52:45,333
<i>Truth be told, I want to haveall my arguments only with her.</i>

1378
01:52:45,417 --> 01:52:46,417
Move aside, Munni.

1379
01:52:46,500 --> 01:52:50,792
<i>I had wronged her greatly,but she stayed with me despite that.</i>

1380
01:52:51,542 --> 01:52:52,375
<i>And today…</i>

1381
01:52:52,458 --> 01:52:53,708
I've got everything.

1382
01:52:54,500 --> 01:52:56,375
<i>…today I can do anything for Rani!</i>

1383
01:52:57,125 --> 01:52:59,250
Welcome home, Rishu.

1384
01:52:59,333 --> 01:53:02,250
We were talking about you.
Did you get the cashews and raisins?

1385
01:53:02,333 --> 01:53:03,417
Please leave, Neel.

1386
01:53:03,500 --> 01:53:04,583
Tell him.

1387
01:53:05,750 --> 01:53:08,083
Tell him that you're leaving with me.
Go on.

1388
01:53:08,167 --> 01:53:09,375
You're lying.

1389
01:53:09,458 --> 01:53:10,708
I'm lying?

1390
01:53:10,792 --> 01:53:14,083
Rishu, he's here to bother us,
nothing else.

1391
01:53:14,167 --> 01:53:16,000
I'm here to bother you?

1392
01:53:16,083 --> 01:53:18,958
He's the one who's been bothering me.

1393
01:53:19,042 --> 01:53:21,750
Why don't you tell her
what you've been up to, Rishu?

1394
01:53:21,833 --> 01:53:24,542
He'd come to Delhi,
to attack me with a screwdriver.

1395
01:53:25,125 --> 01:53:27,625
Now he's told my neighbors
that I'm a sex offender.

1396
01:53:27,708 --> 01:53:29,125
Me, a sex offender?!

1397
01:53:29,792 --> 01:53:33,958
Why did you guys get married,
if you can't satisfy your wife?

1398
01:53:34,625 --> 01:53:37,375
Then people like me get stuck
being called sex offenders.

1399
01:53:37,458 --> 01:53:39,375
Listen, I came here to clarify.

1400
01:53:39,917 --> 01:53:41,542
Neither of us is an offender.

1401
01:53:41,625 --> 01:53:43,958
What happened between us was consensual.
I didn't force her.

1402
01:53:44,042 --> 01:53:45,542
She's right here. Ask her.

1403
01:53:48,417 --> 01:53:49,750
And it was good.

1404
01:53:49,833 --> 01:53:51,042
I bet she thinks about it too.

1405
01:53:51,125 --> 01:53:54,250
Yes, I think about the
huge mistake that I made…

1406
01:53:54,333 --> 01:53:55,542
this is how I think of it.

1407
01:53:56,833 --> 01:53:57,792
A mistake?

1408
01:53:59,250 --> 01:54:00,583
Why did you come to me, then?

1409
01:54:01,417 --> 01:54:04,958
Because one has to kiss many frogs
before one can find true love.

1410
01:54:05,042 --> 01:54:06,958
And you belong to that category.

1411
01:54:16,708 --> 01:54:17,792
A frog, huh?

1412
01:54:19,208 --> 01:54:21,667
This frog is a big fan of yours, Rani.

1413
01:54:21,750 --> 01:54:23,625
Let me increase your fan base.

1414
01:54:24,250 --> 01:54:28,042
I'd taken a few videos
of us together, remember?

1415
01:54:28,958 --> 01:54:31,125
Let me share these
in a few WhatsApp groups.

1416
01:54:31,208 --> 01:54:32,500
And your fan base will increase.

1417
01:54:32,583 --> 01:54:36,000
Rishu, you better get
some more screwdrivers,

1418
01:54:36,083 --> 01:54:39,917
because you'll have to run after quite
a few boys, who'll watch these videos.

1419
01:54:40,000 --> 01:54:42,292
See this. Don't you look nice?

1420
01:54:43,333 --> 01:54:45,500
Remember? You were having a good time too?

1421
01:54:52,250 --> 01:54:53,333
-Rishu!
-Get off!

1422
01:55:02,833 --> 01:55:04,500
You're completely mad, you know?

1423
01:55:15,333 --> 01:55:16,792
Have you lost your mind?

1424
01:55:32,833 --> 01:55:33,958
Rishu…

1425
01:55:34,708 --> 01:55:35,583
Get up.

1426
01:55:42,625 --> 01:55:44,125
There's blood.

1427
01:55:49,792 --> 01:55:50,792
Neel?

1428
01:55:56,917 --> 01:55:58,375
Neel?

1429
01:56:00,375 --> 01:56:01,375
Neel!

1430
01:56:02,750 --> 01:56:03,750
Neel!

1431
01:56:32,167 --> 01:56:33,458
Let me call the police.

1432
01:56:34,083 --> 01:56:36,167
-I'll call the police.
-What?

1433
01:56:36,250 --> 01:56:37,333
He is dead.

1434
01:56:38,542 --> 01:56:41,500
-He is dead.
-No… don't call the police.

1435
01:56:41,583 --> 01:56:43,500
-I killed him.
-You didn't kill him, Rani.

1436
01:56:44,250 --> 01:56:46,000
I killed him, Rishu.

1437
01:56:46,083 --> 01:56:47,708
It was an accident.
He died in an accident.

1438
01:56:47,792 --> 01:56:49,292
We didn't kill him on purpose.

1439
01:56:49,792 --> 01:56:53,208
I won't let you go to jail for this.

1440
01:56:55,292 --> 01:56:58,750
You won't go to jail for this.
Listen carefully.

1441
01:56:58,833 --> 01:57:02,000
Finally, things have improved between us

1442
01:57:03,542 --> 01:57:05,000
and I want to be with you.

1443
01:57:16,042 --> 01:57:17,000
Now…

1444
01:57:19,417 --> 01:57:20,917
what next?

1445
01:57:21,000 --> 01:57:21,958
What do we do?

1446
01:57:25,792 --> 01:57:28,583
In every unplanned crime,
you get one chance to hide it.

1447
01:57:31,792 --> 01:57:34,000
I've read only one of
Dinesh Pandit's novels,

1448
01:57:34,083 --> 01:57:35,083
<i>Wrath of Kasauli.</i>

1449
01:57:38,208 --> 01:57:39,583
-Rishu. No.
-We have no other option.

1450
01:57:39,667 --> 01:57:41,542
No Rishu, this is madness.

1451
01:57:41,625 --> 01:57:42,958
-We don't have a choice, Rani.
-I'll go to jail…

1452
01:57:43,042 --> 01:57:44,792
Nothing will happen.
No one will get caught.

1453
01:57:44,875 --> 01:57:45,750
Listen to me, please.

1454
01:57:45,833 --> 01:57:47,417
Everything will be fine!

1455
01:57:48,167 --> 01:57:49,542
No, I refuse to be parted from you.

1456
01:57:50,167 --> 01:57:51,500
Just do as I say, okay?

1457
01:57:52,792 --> 01:57:53,875
Please.

1458
01:57:55,958 --> 01:57:56,917
We will get caught.

1459
01:58:17,083 --> 01:58:18,125
Ice, ice!

1460
01:58:20,000 --> 01:58:20,875
Ice!

1461
01:58:21,458 --> 01:58:23,042
Go and get some ice!

1462
01:58:26,500 --> 01:58:28,125
Ice… Where's the ice?

1463
01:58:33,083 --> 01:58:33,958
Rani!

1464
01:58:35,417 --> 01:58:36,250
Rani!

1465
01:58:40,167 --> 01:58:42,000
Get some kerosene. Go.

1466
01:58:47,917 --> 01:58:49,458
Get some newspapers.

1467
01:58:51,625 --> 01:58:52,583
Give them to me.

1468
01:59:44,125 --> 01:59:45,875
No, I can't. No.

1469
01:59:49,083 --> 01:59:50,500
Hold this, Rani.

1470
01:59:52,167 --> 01:59:54,083
What's wrong with you, Rani?

1471
01:59:54,167 --> 01:59:55,750
-Please.
-I can't.

1472
01:59:57,417 --> 01:59:59,458
Want to be away from me? No, right?

1473
02:00:01,292 --> 02:00:03,458
Then you have to do this. Do this for us.

1474
02:00:03,958 --> 02:00:05,125
Please, Rani. Okay?

1475
02:00:05,208 --> 02:00:06,375
Come.

1476
02:00:08,125 --> 02:00:09,125
Hold this!

1477
02:00:09,958 --> 02:00:11,500
Rani! Just do it!

1478
02:00:27,875 --> 02:00:30,208
Rishu! Rishu!

1479
02:00:30,833 --> 02:00:33,625
Open your eyes! Open your eyes!

1480
02:00:34,167 --> 02:00:36,000
Open your eyes, Rishu.

1481
02:00:40,625 --> 02:00:41,667
Rishu.

1482
02:00:58,000 --> 02:01:04,208
<i>Your tears are the reason for my sorrows</i>

1483
02:01:04,292 --> 02:01:09,750
<i>Your happiness, I owe to you</i>

1484
02:01:10,375 --> 02:01:16,250
<i>Every inch of my being</i>

1485
02:01:16,333 --> 02:01:21,000
<i>Says that</i>

1486
02:01:22,833 --> 02:01:25,958
<i>We write our own story</i>

1487
02:01:26,042 --> 02:01:29,000
<i>We are our destiny</i>

1488
02:01:29,083 --> 02:01:34,125
<i>We only have each other</i>

1489
02:01:34,208 --> 02:01:37,458
<i>Sorrows are gone</i>

1490
02:01:37,542 --> 02:01:40,583
<i>Happiness is ours</i>

1491
02:01:41,167 --> 02:01:46,208
<i>We've made it together at last</i>

1492
02:01:46,292 --> 02:01:49,333
<i>You've come to me</i>

1493
02:01:49,417 --> 02:01:52,333
<i>Like we've never been apart</i>

1494
02:01:52,417 --> 02:01:56,083
<i>You've come to me</i>

1495
02:01:58,333 --> 02:02:01,250
<i>Love has blossomed</i>

1496
02:02:01,333 --> 02:02:04,125
<i>Like things were never amiss</i>

1497
02:02:04,708 --> 02:02:08,542
<i>Love has blossomed</i>

1498
02:02:09,333 --> 02:02:13,792
<i>You are mine</i>

1499
02:02:26,083 --> 02:02:28,292
Rickshaw!

1500
02:02:35,208 --> 02:02:37,833
Munni, tell Rishu to lock the door.

1501
02:02:39,000 --> 02:02:42,625
Rishu! Rishu! Lock the door!

1502
02:02:43,125 --> 02:02:43,958
Rishu…

1503
02:02:46,250 --> 02:02:49,125
I am making <i>kheer</i> today.
I'll send some over.

1504
02:02:55,208 --> 02:02:56,625
Don't play over here.

1505
02:02:58,333 --> 02:02:59,875
Go somewhere else.

1506
02:03:25,083 --> 02:03:26,417
Wait a minute.

1507
02:03:26,500 --> 02:03:28,958
Give it to me,
I'll get it cut from somewhere else.

1508
02:03:36,042 --> 02:03:37,000
There's one more.

1509
02:03:37,542 --> 02:03:39,125
Can you cut this as well, please?

1510
02:03:40,167 --> 02:03:41,542
DINESH PANDIT
<i>WRATH OF KASAULI</i>

1511
02:03:57,625 --> 02:03:58,667
DINESH PANDIT

1512
02:04:59,750 --> 02:05:00,958
Rishu.

1513
02:05:46,708 --> 02:05:50,000
RANI

1514
02:06:08,250 --> 02:06:12,333
<i>And Bhairav's story of love and sacrifice…</i>

1515
02:06:14,292 --> 02:06:16,500
<i>drowned in the river with him.</i>

1516
02:06:27,583 --> 02:06:29,417
What happened? Why are you laughing?

1517
02:06:30,000 --> 02:06:32,625
He switched the lover's body
with his own and turned the case around.

1518
02:06:35,500 --> 02:06:37,167
<i>The lover will remain missing.</i>

1519
02:06:37,250 --> 02:06:38,417
<i>His body will never be found.</i>

1520
02:06:39,208 --> 02:06:42,458
The husband cut off his hand
and kept it with the dead body,

1521
02:06:43,375 --> 02:06:44,958
to save his wife.

1522
02:06:45,042 --> 02:06:48,250
In this day and age,
who goes to such lengths for love?

1523
02:06:48,333 --> 02:06:51,000
I'm sure, you wouldn't even sacrifice
a fingernail for me!

1524
02:06:58,292 --> 02:07:00,375
DINESH PANDIT
